    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Summarize long emails with PostgreSQL and Twilio hands-free\n\n**Pattern:** AI Summarize & Route · **Level:** Advanced · **Trigger:** Webhook\n\n## What it does\nSummarize long emails with PostgreSQL and Twilio hands-free. It fires the moment an external system calls its webhook.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual embeddings is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nReceive Inbound Webhook → Normalize Document Payload → Detect Sentiment → Escalate Negative — Twilio → Collect All Outcomes → Sort Documents Newest First → Guard Non-Empty title → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to ai summarize & route without manual effort\n- Anyone automating embeddings in ai\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Standardizes the process every time\n- Removes copy-paste errors\n- Keeps your systems in sync\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Anthropic API key; Postgres connection; Twilio SID + token.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "3b6f2009-afec-bde7-e502-aec6da287210",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -500
      ],
      "id": "ce13a344-2ce6-daa0-55d0-c9c871d2995c",
      "name": "🛟 Error handling & retries"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🔐 Security\n\nNever trust inbound payloads: the webhook path is unguessable. Add header auth or IP allow-listing for defense in depth. Secrets live in n8n credentials — never in node parameters.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 1
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        190,
        -500
      ],
      "id": "9241c677-1246-0b35-9809-ba37eca655f0",
      "name": "🔐 Security"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🤖 AI cluster\n\nPurple nodes form one AI unit: the root node orchestrates, sub-nodes plug in via typed ports (model / memory / tools / parser). Swap the chat model without rewiring anything else. Costs scale with tokens — keep prompts lean and cap iterations.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 6
      },
